<h3><b>There are six fields in the file which are explained below.</b>
<h3><b>In order to schedule a process you have to give commands for your process in the format given below.</b>

<table>

<tr>      # Example of job definition:                                                          </tr><br>
<tr>      # .---------------- minute (0 - 59)                                                   </tr><br>
<tr>      # |  .------------- hour (0 - 23)                                                     </tr><br>
<tr>      # |  |  .---------- day of month (1 - 31)                                             </tr><br>
<tr>      # |  |  |  .------- month (1 - 12) OR jan,feb,mar,apr ...                             </tr><br>
<tr>      # |  |  |  |  .---- day of week (0 - 6) (Sunday=0 or 7) OR sun,mon,tue,wed,thu,fri,sat</tr><br>
<tr>      # |  |  |  |  |                                                                       </tr><br>
<tr>      #12  19 *  *  * ls                                                                    </tr><br>
</table> 
#A sample command is given for your reference 
#52 18 * * * /bin/mkdir  /root/Desktop/laksh
#The above command will make a folder in the /root/Desktop directory at around 18:52 hours.

</body>

